Requires Node.Js v16.6.0 or higher

Make sure to run:
	npm init -y
	npm install discord.js @discordjs/builders @discordjs/rest discord-api-types

Add your configuration info into a file 'config.json':

{
	"token": "your-token-goes-here",
	"clientId": "your-clientId-goes-here",
	"guildId": "your-guildId-goes-here"
}

Once you've done that you can deploy any commands by running:
	node deployCommands.js

And then you're bot is ready to be brought online, run:
	node index.js

Go ahead and try a slash command in your test server:
	/ping

You should get a response... if not, you did sum'n wrong
